application_type_full: Outline planning permission: Some matters reserved
description: Application for the Imperial West ('Woodlands') site comprising detailed application for 3 buildings: 1) academic (9 storeys/23,077m2 GEA) (Class D1) including health research, day nursery (1,029sqm GIA) (Class D1) and restaurant (2,127sqm GIA) (Class A3); 2) office and research units (part 6, part 12 storeys/22,528m2 GEA) (Class B1) of which 390sqm (GIA) Class A3; and 3) residential tower (Class C3) (35 storeys/20,297m2 GEA) of 192 units (59 of which are key worker units) and 319sqm (GIA) of A1/A3 floorspace; along with an access road, car/cycle parking, ancillary plant and landscaping; Outline application for 3 additional buildings; 1) hotel (13 storeys/ 14,500m2 GEA) (Class C1) including 1,080sqm (GIA) restaurant (Class A1/A3) and 850sqm (GIA) fitness centre (Class D2); 2) education (7 storeys/maximum 6,500m2 GEA) (Class D1) of which 600sqm (GIA) Class A1/A3; and B1 and 3) administrative (Part 3, part 5 storeys/maximum 5,900m2 GEA). Demolition of existing sports hall and office.
